ROCm MoE prefill: WMMA_I8 via lazy per-batch weight repack (proof first)

Status: Open (started 2026-05-09).

Goal
Land WMMA_I8 routed-MoE prefill backed by a per-prefill-batch lazy repack of
active experts (IQ2_XXS gate/up + Q2_K down -> Q8_0-shaped int8+fp16scale
in scratch). Reuse activation microquant from tsk-25.

Motivation
- Routed MoE is the dominant slice of prefill compute and currently runs the
  wave-per-row IQ2/Q2 kernels designed for decode (188 GiB/s = DRAM ceiling),
  which leaves ALU on the table at higher n_tok where weights amortize.
- WMMA_I8 prefill on Q8_0-shaped weights gave 1.6-3.6x in the dense matmul
  microbench (tsk-25). MoE prefill should see similar lever.
- Eager full-pool repack to int8 inflates ~26 GB IQ2/Q2 -> ~188 GB Q8_0,
  doesn't fit in 96 GB UMA. Per-prefill-batch lazy repack of active experts
  fits (peak ~300 MB/layer step at production dims).

Key risk
EM (expert-major) layout reorg lost at n_tokens=21 (29.7->26.3 t/s) per the
in-source note at ds4_rocm.c:6238-6249. If the underlying limiter at 21 tokens
is launch overhead or scheduling, WMMA_I8 won't help either. Need a
microbench-driven proof before committing the full pipeline.

Plan
Stage 1 (proof): repack kernels + microbench measuring
  (a) repack throughput per expert (target: <1 ms/expert at production dims)
  (b) wave-per-row IQ2_XXS gate_up matvec at n_tok=21
  (c) WMMA_I8 gate_up matvec at n_tok=21 from pre-repacked Q8_0 scratch
  Project total cost (repack + WMMA) vs (b). Decision gate: >=20% savings
  at n_tok=21 to proceed with Stage 2.
Stage 2: wire repack + WMMA_I8 into rocm_moe_run behind DS4_ROCM_MOE_WMMA=1.
  Reuse rocm_moe_group_pairs_kernel + g_moe_em_scratch_d. Add a parallel
  scratch slab for repacked Q8_0 weights.
Stage 3: kernel tests + end-to-end coherence + benchmark; set default if
  positive at canonical prompt size.

Validation
- ./ds4_rocm_kernel_test must end with OK (40 tests + new repack tests).
- ./ds4 --backend rocm -p "Briefly explain..." -n 200 --temp 0 --seed 42
  must produce coherent multi-paragraph thinking-mode reply.
- Capture prefill/decode t/s before and after each commit.

